Keith -

The transport property formulas are essentially those described in the  
Kee, Coltrin, Glarborg book.

The error &lt;no cantera error&gt; means that an exceotion was caught, but it  
wasn;t one thrown by Cantera. I suspect this problem is occurring in  
the evaluation of collision integrals. These are evaluated by  
polynomial interpolation from tables published by Monchick and Mason.   
Probably the non-dimensional temperature T* is going out of range. Or  
else there is a problem with delta* for H2O, if you are including water  
in your mixture.  The log file transport_log.xml might contain some  
clues.

I should probably add a transport option to skip the usual formulas and  
just interpolatae from user-input data values.

Dave

